There are ripple effects to technology and a technological society

Where does software start?

When we start thinking about what we want to achieve

Tests can be considered a way that we ask questions about our code

Of course part of the problem of viewing it this way is that we cannot cover every expectation with tests

Why ship fast? We quickly make sure that we are meeting the user's needs. 

Shipping fast helps us answer questions that tests cannot

A key bit of feedback could be if you have customers with accessibilty features because you don't have the expertise on your team. But you also need to make sure you know how to get feedback from those users. 

What are the goals of the system? Are we asking the right questions of the right people?


